Kenya Breweries Limited, through the Tusker trademark, held the Tusker Oktoba Fest last weekend at the Ngong Racecourse. The festival, a first of its kind, ran for two days and was filled with a sea of humanity. It ran from October 5-6 and had an all-Kenyan entertainment line-up of 39 acts. These included Khaligraph Jones, Sauti Sol, Nyashinksi, Jua Cali, Fena, The Kansoul, Bensoul, Nadia Mukami, Sailors, Ethic, Ochunglo Family, Samido and H_art the band.